Java is a well-known, general-purpose, object-oriented programming language that's used to create applications for many different types of devices and platforms. It's been popular with developers for over 20 years, and is used to create applications for mobile devices, the web, gaming, big data, and more. Java is also a computing platform that was first released in 1995 by Sun Microsystems. 

Java can be used across many different platforms, including Windows, Linux, and Mac. 
Java is a high-level language that's easy to understand. 

With Java, developers can compile code that will run on any Java-compatible platform without needing to recompile it. 

